v 3
d cnadmin. Matching Chinese Administrative Divisions Across Years
d 
d cnadmin is a Python-backed Stata command that tracks the historical 
d changes of China's administrative codes and names (e.g., county-to-district 
d upgrades, mergers, and complex splits). Utilizing a temporal Directed 
d Acyclic Graph (DAG), it supports both forward and backward tracing 
d and automatically generates proper apportionment weights for 1-to-N splits 
d to prevent data attrition.
d 
